On Fri, Sep 12, 2008 at 12:39 PM, adrian.kuhn &lt;adrian.kuhn@...&gt; wrote:
&gt; This is a JUnit issue as well. I have the same issue with JExample: if a
&gt; test has parameters, you can rerun a single test, but not browse it.
&gt;
&gt; Why does this happen? The plugin works with the org.junit.runner.Description
&gt; that it gets from JUnit. Such a description contains a mere string rather
&gt; than a reference to a java method, thus the plugin must guess about the
&gt; strings format when trying to locate the method for browsing.

Can you (or an interested observer) open a bug against Eclipse for
this?  Custom runners can of course make the descriptions whatever
they want (the test may not refer to any Java method at all), but it
seems that methodName[OTHER_INFORMATION] is a reasonable template that
Eclipse should respect.

Thanks!

   David

